cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks using contextual word embeddings, which are commonly studied in the computer science subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as adversarial learning, which falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the alignment of embeddings, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The tasks evaluated in the paper, text classification and named entity recognition, are also relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
